David Low's academy aims to get kids involved in all cycling disciplines, groom them and nurture the young enthusiasts. eNCA’s Siphokazi Malinga reports. #DStv403 PIETERMARITZBURG - Greg Minnaar is South Africa’s most successful downhill mountain biker. His journey might have started in Pietermaritzburg but he has gone on to represent South Africa at international level. David Low was inspired by this to open a cycling academy in Pietermaritzburg. The academy aims to get kids involved in all cycling disciplines, groom them and nurture the young enthusiasts. At the moment his cyclists are busy preparing for the South African Champs set to take place next month. * eNCA’s Siphokazi Malinga reports.